\p
\v 6 And it was the day, and the sons of God came to present themselves to Yahweh. And the adversary also came in the midst of them.
\v 7 And Yahweh said to the adversary, “From where have you come?” And the adversary answered Yahweh and said, “From wandering on the earth and from going back and forth on it.”
\v 8 And Yahweh said to the adversary, “Have you set your heart upon my servant Job? For {there is} not like him on the earth, a blameless and righteous man, fearful of God and turning from evil.”

\v 9 And the adversary answered Yahweh and said, “Does Job fear God for nothing?
\v 10 Have you not put a hedge around him and around his house and around all that {is} his, from every side? You have blessed the works of his hands, and his cattle have burst forth in the land.
\v 11 However, just stretch out your hand and touch all that {is} his, if he will not bless you to your face.”
\v 12 And Yahweh said to the adversary, “Behold, all that {is} his {is} in your hand. Only against him do not stretch out your hand.” And the adversary went away from the face of Yahweh.

\p
\v 13 And it was the day, and his sons and his daughters {were} eating and drinking wine in the house of their eldest brother.
\v 14 And a messenger came to Job and said, “The oxen were plowing and the donkeys {were} feeding at their hand.
\v 15 And Sheba fell {on them} and took them, and they struck the servants with the edge of the sword, and only I alone have escaped to tell you.”

\v 16 That one {was} still speaking and another came and said, “The fire of God fell from the heavens and burned up the sheep and the servants and consumed them, and only I alone have escaped to tell you.”
